# ios-backup-parser — single source of truth for the toolchain version + image refs.
#
# Consumed in exactly two places:
#   - Makefile   `include versions.env`   → runs the gates inside these images
#   - Dockerfile via `--build-arg` passed by the Makefile (defaults mirror these)
#
# The dev host is a pure container host (no Go toolchain installed anywhere): the
# gates run in the pinned toolchain container built from deploy/Dockerfile. Bumps
# land HERE.
#
# Pins are looked up live at bump time (house rule), never remembered:
#   Go 1.26.5            — latest stable (go.dev/dl, verified 2026-07-20)
#   golangci-lint 2.12.2 — latest stable v2 (github.com/golangci/golangci-lint, 2026-07-20)
#   Alpine 3.24          — house Alpine line; the -alpine3.24 Go variant exists
#   modernc.org/sqlite v1.54.0 — latest (proxy.golang.org, 2026-07-20); pinned in go.mod

# --- Versions (human-facing pins) ---
GO_VERSION=1.26.5
GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION=2.12.2
ALPINE_VERSION=3.24

# --- Toolchain image (the gate container == the toolchain-go Dockerfile stage) ---
GO_IMAGE=golang:1.26.5-alpine3.24
ALPINE_IMAGE=alpine:3.24

# --- Differential oracle (testing ladder rung 3): iLEAPP, run as an installed tool
# in its own container. iLEAPP is MIT (see NOTICE) — unlike the GPL oracles it MAY
# be read and cloned; it still lives only inside the container image, never in this
# repo's tree. Not on PyPI: the image clones the release tag and installs its
# requirements. v2026.1.0 is the latest release (github.com/abrignoni/iLEAPP,
# verified 2026-07-20). Python 3.12, NOT the newest 3.13: iLEAPP's requirements
# pin numpy 1.26.x, which ships no cp313 wheels (build attempt verified failing
# 2026-07-20) — the oracle's floor wins over the newest-stable rule here.
PYTHON_IMAGE=python:3.12-slim
ILEAPP_VERSION=v2026.1.0
